signify some particular class of syllable which would include about
three-fourths of the whole number of syllables. It may be noted,
however, that Zâ*d*-sparam, in the particulars he gives about the Gâthas
(see SZS. XI, 10, note 6), states the number of mârîk at 6666. The
khûr*d*ak or 'small' things are probably the consonants.

<span id="fn_1837"></span>[369:1](sbe0573.htm#fr_1849.md) All MSS. have
